Subject: [PATCH 2/4] ICE: address review feedback on wait-valid-pair grace
 timer

- TIMER_WAIT_VALID_PAIR no longer fails ICE unconditionally on expiry. If
  checks are still pending (e.g. a triggered check from a late incoming check
  is in progress) or valid pairs have meanwhile been created, defer to the
  normal completion handling instead of forcing PJNATH_EICEFAILED.
- Fix option docs: the grace timer is armed when one or more components still
  lack a valid pair (not only when no component has one).

